column5: 148 days until we step off the plane at Brace Lake Outfitters.
I sent my deposit this week. My daughter and I will going for the 3rd year to Pickerel Arm Camp on Minnetaki June 14-21.http://i936.photobucket.com/albums/a...r/IMG_7521.jpg

217 days to lake Windermere. Hate to wait that long but that's life. I think it's harder on my 12 yo then me. On the plus side he shows me every good walleye video he finds and that saves me a lot of time. Also Mom sees it as bonding so she's cool with us watching fishing shows. That's real different.
June 7 - 14 , Camp Grassy Narrows , Lac Simard, Moffet, Quebec

dave you guys have fished a lot of places and I value your opinion have you guys ever fished stokes fishing camp on canadian side side of rainy lake and also checked out a fly in outpost called wilderness 7 camps base camp from which they fly out of 2 hrs north of thunder a local guy stated the fly in lakes are great checking the website really like dusey lake out post;have a call into owner and will report if you or any other fishermen have fished or hear reports about these 2 camps I would appreciate your input probably going 2nd or 3rd week of sept have paided deposit for last of may at black bear camp on red lake jim wolf chicago boys

141 and a wakeup to Frog Rapids Camp in mid June and 170 and a wakeup for the July trip, also to Frog Rapids, with my Dad, a long-timer, and a couple Indiana greenhorns.
Only 190 days to go now! Its warmer at Red Lake today than it is here in Central Il.!?
Looking forward to a report on this -- Talston is on my bucket list! 232 days to SWWL on Lac Seul.
141 days, 11 hours, 55 minutes, 43 seconds. Headed to Big Canon. Biggest Group ever 15 guys. Going to need a separate trailer for the booze.

Second trip with Parks Outpost Camps.Last June we had a great trip to ABBEY LAKE and like different Lakes each Year.Flying out of Chapleau.Hope everyone has a great fishing Season.Been doing Fly-Ins since 1966, thats when you had to pump out the pontoons so you could get off the water!! Last Year at Abbey was one of the most productive fishing weeks I have had ( for numbers, not size) in many, many Years. Second to them would have been 4 years ago up to Pasha Lake.

May 30th-June 8. My 3rd trip with Mike and Renae at PFO. Camoclad and myself with 6 others will slay some eyes! Going to Kenoji lake which is known for huge pike and good numbers on walleye as well. Can't wait!
Parks Fly IN to Anjigaming Lake -- June 21 to 28 ... First time with Parks! Been doing fly ins for over 25 years!
Lac Seul Lodge with my wife and two sons June 28. Then flying in to Bauer's camp on Onaman with one of my sons on August 3.
May 30th to June 8th, Gouin Resevoir, Oasis du Gouin. Pumped!
I'm green with envy!!
It's only money..............I have a lot of tackle organized already. It will make the winter go by a little quicker.
I expect reports and photo's, photo's, and more photo's!!!
Yea, Im a little late this year, but so is my trip to Black Bear Lodge on Red Lake. 199 days before we hit the first walleye ! How about your trip? How many days, and where ya goin?
